<paragraph blockId="17.[151,751,220,244]" box="[151,751,220,244]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName authority="Moulds 2018" authorityName="Marshall &amp; Moulds" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,440,220,244]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Macrotristriini">Macrotristriini Moulds 2018</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, D. C. &amp; Moulds, M. S. &amp; Hill, K. B. R. &amp; Price, B. W. &amp; Wade, E. J. &amp; Owen, C. J. &amp; Goemans, G. &amp; Marathe, K. &amp; Sarkar, V. &amp; Cooley, J. R. &amp; Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Kunte, K. &amp; Villet, M. H. &amp; Simon, C." box="[481,702,220,244]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref69587" refString="Marshall, D. C., Moulds, M. S., Hill, K. B. R., Price, B. W., Wade, E. J., Owen, C. J., Goemans, G., Marathe, K., Sarkar, V., Cooley, J. R., Sanborn, A. F., Kunte, K., Villet, M. H. &amp; Simon, C. (2018 b) A molecular phylogeny of the cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) with a review of tribe and subfamily level classification. Zootaxa, 4424 (1), 1 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4424.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">
Marshall 
<emphasis box="[577,621,220,244]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2018b
</bibRefCitation>
): 44.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,290,497]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Remarks.—The tribe was recently erected based on a five gene phylogenetic tree to incorporate two Australian genera, one of which includes a species from 
<collectingCountry box="[669,804,326,352]" name="Madagascar" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, D. C. &amp; Moulds, M. S. &amp; Hill, K. B. R. &amp; Price, B. W. &amp; Wade, E. J. &amp; Owen, C. J. &amp; Goemans, G. &amp; Marathe, K. &amp; Sarkar, V. &amp; Cooley, J. R. &amp; Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Kunte, K. &amp; Villet, M. H. &amp; Simon, C." box="[819,1068,326,353]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref69587" refString="Marshall, D. C., Moulds, M. S., Hill, K. B. R., Price, B. W., Wade, E. J., Owen, C. J., Goemans, G., Marathe, K., Sarkar, V., Cooley, J. R., Sanborn, A. F., Kunte, K., Villet, M. H. &amp; Simon, C. (2018 b) A molecular phylogeny of the cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) with a review of tribe and subfamily level classification. Zootaxa, 4424 (1), 1 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4424.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">
Marshall 
<emphasis box="[929,979,326,352]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2018b
</bibRefCitation>
). Species of the tribe can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[399,511,362,388]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cicadinae">Cicadinae</taxonomicName>
by possessing a head with an elongated vertex so that the distance between the eye and supra-antennal plate is much longer than the length of the supra-antennal plate, male timbal covers are flat and reach the metathorax anteriorly but are a little reduced dorsally, and theca with one or two subapical theca (Marshall 
<emphasis box="[151,200,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2018).
</paragraph>
